      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Patrick Winston</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"http://sixminutes.dlugan.com/2008/03/24/speaking-tips-patrick-henry-winston-speak/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/a/a3/How-to-speak-patrick-winston.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:How-to-speak-patrick-winston.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Patrick Winston <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Patrick Henry Winston</b>,<br />\nan American computer scientist and professor of <a href=\"/Artificial_Intelligence\" title=\"Artificial Intelligence\">Artificial Intelligence</a> at <a href=\"/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">Massachusetts Institute of Technology</a>, where he already obtained his Ph.D. in 1970 under <a href=\"/Marvin_Minsky\" title=\"Marvin Minsky\">Marvin Minsky</a>, concerning the difficulty of <a href=\"/Learning\" title=\"Learning\">machine learning</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>.\nHis book <i>Artificial Intelligence</i> covers the broad range of AI-Issues <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>, including <a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">Search</a>, <a href=\"/Alpha-Beta\" title=\"Alpha-Beta\">Alpha-Beta</a> and <a href=\"/Learning\" title=\"Learning\">Learning</a>. \nWinston is also author of various books on <a href=\"/Programming\" title=\"Programming\">Programming Languages</a>, such as <a href=\"/Java\" title=\"Java\">Java</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Smalltalk&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Smalltalk (page does not exist)\">Smalltalk</a>, <a href=\"/C\" title=\"C\">C</a>, <a href=\"/Cpp\" title=\"Cpp\">C++</a> and <a href=\"/index.php?title=Lisp&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Lisp (page does not exist)\">Lisp</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1970_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1970 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#1980_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1980 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#1990_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1990 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Patrick_Winston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1970_...\">1970 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Patrick_Winston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1970 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1970</b>). <i> Learning Structural Descriptions from Examples</i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a href=\"/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">MIT</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1975</b>). <i>The Psychology of Computer Vision</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McGraw-Hill_Education\">McGraw-Hill</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1976</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/The-psychology-of-computer-vision-Winston/9aad8a4c8a94209beb49d97a40c0e6deeffa50e7\">The psychology of computer vision</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pattern_Recognition_(journal)\">Pattern Recognition</a>, Vol. 8, No. 3</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#ARosenfeld\" title=\"Mathematician\">Azriel Rosenfeld</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#JeromeFeldman\" title=\"Mathematician\">Jerome A. Feldman</a>, <a href=\"/Laveen_Kanal\" title=\"Laveen Kanal\">Laveen N. Kanal</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick H. Winston</a> (<b>1977</b>). <i>AI and Pattern Recognition</i>. <a href=\"/Conferences#IJCAI1977\" title=\"Conferences\">IJCAI 1977</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i>Dealing with Adversaries</i>. <a href=\"/Personal_Computing#2_11\" title=\"Personal Computing\">Personal Computing, Vol. 2, No. 11</a>, pp. 30, November 1978&#160;» <a href=\"/Alpha-Beta\" title=\"Alpha-Beta\">Alpha-Beta</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>Artificial Intelligence</i>. 1st Edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addison-Wesley\">Addison-Wesley</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1980_...\">1980 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Patrick_Winston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 1980 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1980</b>). <i>Learning and Reasoning by Analogy</i>. <a href=\"/ACM#Communications\" title=\"ACM\">Communications of the ACM</a>, Vol. 23, No. 12</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1983</b>). <i>Artificial Intelligence Research at the Artificial Intelligence Laboratory, Massachusetts Institute of Technology</i>. <a href=\"/AAAI#AIMAG\" title=\"AAAI\">AI Magazine</a>, Vol. 4, No. 2</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>Artificial Intelligence</i>. 2nd Edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addison-Wesley\">Addison-Wesley</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Ryszard_Michalski\" title=\"Ryszard Michalski\">Ryszard Michalski</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>Variable Precision Logic</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_Intelligence_(journal)\">Artificial Intelligence</a>, Vol. 29, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mli.gmu.edu/papers/86-90/86-29.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#BKPHorn\" title=\"Mathematician\">Berthold K. P. Horn</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/Books/index.html#Lisp\">LISP</a></i>. 3rd Edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addison-Wesley\">Addison-Wesley</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1990_...\">1990 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Patrick_Winston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 1990 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1992</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/Books/AIBACK.HTML\">Artificial Intelligence</a>.</i> 3rd Edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pearson_Education\">Pearson</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1995</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/Books/index.html#OnToC++\">On To C++</a></i>. 2nd Edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/OnToCPP/\">online</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1997</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/Books/index.html#OnToSt\">On To Smalltalk</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addison-Wesley\">Addison-Wesley</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Patrick_Winston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>2001</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/Books/index.html#OnToJava\">On To Java</a></i>. 3rd Edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pearson_Education\">Pearson</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#NLCassimatis\" title=\"Mathematician\">Nicholas L. Cassimatis</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#ETMueller\" title=\"Mathematician\">Erik T. Mueller</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>2006</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.aaai.org/ojs/index.php/aimagazine/article/view/1876\">Achieving Human-Level Intelligence through Integrated Systems and Research: Introduction to This Special Issue</a></i>. <a href=\"/AAAI#AIMAG\" title=\"AAAI\">AI Magazine</a>, Vol. 27, No. 2 </li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Patrick_Winston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>2011</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dspace.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/67693\">The Strong Story Hypothesis and the Directed Perception Hypothesis</a></i>. <a href=\"/AAAI\" title=\"AAAI\">AAAI</a> Advances in Cognitive Systems 2011</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>2015</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dspace.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/99102\">Model-based Story Summary</a></i>. 6th International Workshop on Computational Models of Narrative</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Henry Winston</a> (<b>2016</b>). <i>Marvin L. Minsky (1927-2016)</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nature_%28journal%29\">Nature</a>, Vol. 530&#160;» <a href=\"/Marvin_Minsky\" title=\"Marvin Minsky\">Marvin Minsky</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Patrick_Winston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/index.html\">Patrick Henry Winston Homepage</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patrick_Winston\">Patrick Winston from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://genealogy.math.ndsu.nodak.edu/id.php?id=61072\">Patrick Winston - The Mathematics Genealogy Project</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"AI_Lectures\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/electrical-engineering-and-computer-science/6-034-artificial-intelligence-fall-2010/lecture-videos/\">Lecture Videos | Artificial Intelligence | Electrical Engineering and Computer Science | MIT OpenCourseWare</a>, <a href=\"/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">MIT</a> 6.034 <a href=\"/Artificial_Intelligence\" title=\"Artificial Intelligence\">Artificial Intelligence</a>, by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a>, Fall 2010, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YouTube\">YouTube</a> Videos</li></ul>\n<ol><li> <span id=\"Lecture_1\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TjZBTDzGeGg\">Introduction and Scope</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_2\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PNKj529yY5c\">Reasoning: Goal Trees and Problem Solving</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_3\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=leXa7EKUPFk\">Reasoning: Goal Trees and Rule-Based Expert Systems</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_4\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j1H3jAAGlEA\">Search: Depth-First, Hill Climbing, Beam</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_5\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gGQ-vAmdAOI\">Search: Optimal, Branch and Bound, A*</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_6\"></span><a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">Search</a>: <a href=\"/Games\" title=\"Games\">Games</a>, <a href=\"/Minimax\" title=\"Minimax\">Minimax</a>, and <a href=\"/Alpha-Beta\" title=\"Alpha-Beta\">Alpha-Beta</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> <br /><div class='embedvideo ev_inline ev_top autoResize' style=' width: 646px;'><div class='embedvideowrap' style='width: 640px;'><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/STjW3eH0Cik?\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_7\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l-tzjenXrvI\">Constraints: Interpreting Line Drawings</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_8\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d1KyYyLmGpA\">Constraints: Search, Domain Reduction</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_9\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gvmfbePC2pc\">Constraints: Visual Object Recognition</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_10\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=09mb78oiPkA\">Introduction to Learning, Nearest Neighbors</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_11\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SXBG3RGr_Rc\">Learning: Identification Trees, Disorder</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_12\"></span><a href=\"/Learning\" title=\"Learning\">Learning</a>: <a href=\"/Neural_Networks\" title=\"Neural Networks\">Neural Nets</a>, <a href=\"/Neural_Networks#Backpropagation\" title=\"Neural Networks\">Back Propagation</a><br /><div class='embedvideo ev_inline ev_top autoResize' style=' width: 646px;'><div class='embedvideowrap' style='width: 640px;'><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/q0pm3BrIUFo?\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_13\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kHyNqSnzP8Y\">Learning: Genetic Algorithms</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_14\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L73hY1pBcQI\">Learning: Sparse Spaces, Phonology</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_15\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sh3EPjhhd40\">Learning: Near Misses, Felicity Conditions</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_16\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_PwhiWxHK8o\">Learning: Support Vector Machines</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_17\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UHBmv7qCey4\">Learning: Boosting</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_18\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bQI0OmJPby4\">Representations: Classes, Trajectories, Transitions</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_19\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PimSbFGrwXM\">Architectures: GPS, SOAR, Subsumption, Society of Mind</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_20\"></span>AI business, not available</li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_21\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A6Ud6oUCRak\">Probabilistic Inference I</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_22\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EC6bf8JCpDQ\">Probabilistic Inference II</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"Lecture_23\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XPEJg_6Cg6o\">Model Merging, Cross-Modal Coupling, Course Summary</a></li></ol>\n<ul><li> <span id=\"Lecture_12b\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VrMHA3yX_QI\">Deep Neural Nets</a> (12b 6.034 Fall 2015)<br /><div class='embedvideo ev_inline ev_top autoResize' style=' width: 646px;'><div class='embedvideowrap' style='width: 640px;'><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/VrMHA3yX_QI?\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Patrick_Winston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://sixminutes.dlugan.com/2008/03/24/speaking-tips-patrick-henry-winston-speak/\">How to Speak: 7 Speaking Tips from Patrick Henry Winston</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patrick_Winston\">Patrick Winston from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Patrick Winston</a> (<b>1970</b>). <i> Learning Structural Descriptions from Examples</i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a href=\"/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">MIT</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/Books/AITABLE.HTML\">The Table of Contents for Artificial Intelligence</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/Books/index.html\">Books by Patrick Henry Winston and Friends</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/phw/Books/index.html\">Books by Patrick Henry Winston and Friends</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/w/Winston:Patrick_Henry.html\">dblp: Patrick Henry Winston</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http